cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting biasing misappropriation attacks on distributed observers, which is a topic related to system control and security. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of attack models and decentralized detection, which are topics related to computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves distributed computing and network interconnections, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the use of $H_\infty$ synthesis in the design of attack detectors suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
